quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  35,41,"Truly God maintains the heavens and the earth, lest they fall apart. And were they to fall apart, none would maintain them after Him. Truly He is Clement, Forgiving"
  35,42,"And they swore by God their most solemn oaths that, were a warner to come unto them, they would be more rightly guided than any of the communities. Yet when a warner came unto them, it increased them in naught but aversion"
  35,43,"waxing arrogant upon the earth and plotting evil; yet evil plotting besets none but its authors. So do they await aught but the wont of those of old? Thou shalt find no alteration in the wont of God, and thou shalt find no change in the wont of God"
  35,44,"Have they not journeyed upon the earth and observed how those before them fared in the end, though they were greater than them in strength? Naught in the heavens or upon the earth can thwart God. Truly He is Knowing, Powerful"
  35,45,"Were God to take mankind to task for that which they have earned, He would not leave a single creature upon the surface of the earth. But He grants them reprieve till a term appointed. And when their term comes, truly God sees His servants"
  36,1,Ya. Sin
  36,2,By the Wise Quran
  36,3,truly thou art among the message bearers
  36,4,upon a straight path
  36,5,"a revelation of the Mighty, the Merciful"
  36,6,that thou mayest warn a people whose fathers were not warned; s0 they were heedless
  36,7,"The Word has indeed come due for most of them, for they do not believe"
  36,8,"Truly We have put shackles upon their necks, and they are up to their chins, so that they are forced up"
  36,9,And We placed a barrier before them and a barrier behind them and veiled them; so they see not
  36,10,It is the same for them whether thou warnest them or warnest them not; they do not believe
  36,11,Thou only warnest whomsoever follows the Reminder and fears the Compassionate unseen. So give such a one glad tidings of forgiveness and a generous reward
  36,12,Truly We give life to the dead and record that which they have sent forth and that which they have left behind. And We have counted all things in a clear registry
  36,13,"And set forth for them as a parable the people of the town, when the message bearers came unto it"
  36,14,"When We sent two unto them, they denied them. So We strengthened them with a third, and they said, “Verily, we have been sent unto you!”"
  36,15,"They said, “You are but human beings like us, and the Compassionate has not sent down anything. You are but lying.”"
  36,16,"They said, “Our Lord knows. Verily we have indeed been sent unto you"
  36,17,And naught is incumbent upon us save the clear proclamation.”
  36,18,"They said, “Truly we augur ill of you. If you cease not, we shall certainly stone you, and a painful punishment will certainly befall you from us.”"
  36,19,"They said, “Your auguring ill is upon yourselves though you have been reminded? Nay, you are a prodigal people!”"
  36,20,"And from the outskirts of the city, a man came running. He said, “O my people! Follow the message bearers"
  36,21,Follow those who ask not of you any reward and who are guided
  36,22,"Why should I not worship Him who originated me, and unto Whom you will be returned"
  36,23,"Shall I take gods apart from Him? If the Compassionate desired harm for me, their intercession would avail me naught, nor would they save me"
  36,24,Truly would I then be in manifest error
  36,25,"Truly I believe in your Lord, so listen to me.”"
  36,26,"It was said unto him, “Enter the Garden!” He said, “Would that my people knew"
  36,27,how my Lord forgave me and placed me among the honored.”